    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a low heat and add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span><strong> cold water </strong>and scrape up any meaty bits stuck to your pan with a wooden spoon</p><p>Stir in your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>clotted cream</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong> and <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened to a double cream-like consistency (add a splash of water if it's looking a little thick!) – this is your <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>mustard sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
