        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pot to a medium heat with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> remaining chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add the <strong>cooked green beans </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 1 min further – these are your <strong>garlicky green beans</strong></p><p>Pour any <strong>steak</strong> <strong>resting juices</strong> from the plate into the creamy mustard sauce and slice the <strong>rested steak[s] </strong>finely on a clean board</p>",
